    "code": "package main\n\nfunc editDistance(word1 string, word2 string) int {\n\tm, n := len(word1), len(word2)\n\tdp := make([][]int, m+1)\n\tfor i := range dp {\n\t\tdp[i] = make([]int, n+1)\n\t}\n\tfor i := 0; i <= m; i++ {\n\t\tdp[i][0] = i\n\t}\n\tfor j := 0; j <= n; j++ {\n\t\tdp[0][j] = j\n\t}\n\tfor i := 1; i <= m; i++ {\n\t\tfor j := 1; j <= n; j++ {\n\t\t\tif word1[i-1] == word2[j-1] {\n\t\t\t\tdp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1]\n\t\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t\tdp[i][j] = 1 + min(dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1], dp[i-1][j-1])\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn dp[m][n]\n}\n",
    "notes": "# Notes: Edit Distance\n\n## Status\n- [ ] First pass  [ ] Blind recall  [ ] Interview-ready\n\n## Recall\n- LeetCode: https://leetcode.com/problems/edit-distance/\n- Read the **Visual** line in [`solution.go`](./solution.go) before each blind recall.\n\n## Mistakes\n-\n\n## Revisions\n- YYYY-MM-DD:",
    "approaches": "# Approaches: 13.6 Edit distance\n\n| Approach | File | Time | Space | When |\n|----------|------|------|-------|------|\n| Bottom Up Dp (primary) | `solution.go` | O(m*n) | O(m*n) | Interview default; O(1) or O(n) space rolling |\n| Top-down DP with memo | `variants/top-down-dp.go` | O(m*n) | O(m*n) | Default; recursive flood fill (mutates grid) |\n\nDrill the **primary** blind first. Use variants when an interviewer asks for BFS vs DFS, recursive vs iterative, etc.",
